Description: Fragment of flattened handle at neck join from a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine light pink-brown; white inclusions. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Agelochos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum ABC 0035.36. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 101a, 36
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0394)
